1
00:00:13,549 --> 00:00:15,879
(Jung Ryeo Won)

2
00:00:17,519 --> 00:00:19,850
(Wi Ha Jun)

3
00:00:27,189 --> 00:00:29,959
(Scriptwriter: Park Kyeong Hwa)

4
00:00:30,159 --> 00:00:32,970
(Director: Ahn Pan Seok)

5
00:00:39,740 --> 00:00:44,009
(The Midnight Romance in Hagwon)

6
00:01:03,759 --> 00:01:05,529
I said I'd give you gold and riches.

7
00:01:08,270 --> 00:01:10,600
I said we'd live happily forever and ever.

8
00:01:11,509 --> 00:01:13,009
Don't feel bad for me.

9
00:01:15,080 --> 00:01:16,179
Don't be intimidated.

10
00:01:16,979 --> 00:01:19,750
I don't care about riches or a happy forever.

11
00:01:22,819 --> 00:01:23,850
But...

12
00:01:24,080 --> 00:01:26,520
There's something I need you to do.

13
00:01:33,530 --> 00:01:34,600
Anything.

14
00:01:35,559 --> 00:01:36,860
With all your heart...

15
00:01:38,330 --> 00:01:39,630
and efforts,

16
00:01:42,600 --> 00:01:43,640
love me.

17
00:01:49,179 --> 00:01:50,910
Try to be with me always.

18
00:01:53,479 --> 00:01:55,020
Try to touch and feel me,

19
00:01:55,080 --> 00:01:56,619
and say you want to feed me.

20
00:02:02,319 --> 00:02:03,360
That will do.

21
00:02:43,630 --> 00:02:46,530
(Episode 14)

22
00:03:37,549 --> 00:03:38,690
That will do.

23
00:04:44,890 --> 00:04:46,090
Jun Ho has a girlfriend.

24
00:04:49,559 --> 00:04:51,689
It's his old academy instructor.

25
00:04:55,100 --> 00:04:56,429
Tell me more.

26
00:04:57,229 --> 00:04:59,770
He went to many academies and had many instructors.

27
00:05:00,530 --> 00:05:02,238
His Korean instructor...

28
00:05:02,239 --> 00:05:04,299
from when his grades suddenly shot up.

29
00:05:07,039 --> 00:05:08,410
The one who taught Eun Ho too?

30
00:05:11,150 --> 00:05:12,679
I'm so upset, but...

31
00:05:13,580 --> 00:05:14,879
Why are you upset?

32
00:05:17,549 --> 00:05:18,650
I don't know why.

33
00:05:19,650 --> 00:05:23,220
I want to disapprove, but I can't think of a reason.

34
00:05:25,129 --> 00:05:28,160
Should I complain about her age first?

35
00:05:34,799 --> 00:05:37,770
Call Jun Ho over and talk to him.

36
00:05:38,640 --> 00:05:40,970
You want me to fish for details about my grown son's girlfriend?

37
00:05:41,379 --> 00:05:44,808
I didn't say anything when I first realized...

38
00:05:44,809 --> 00:05:46,210
he was seeing someone.

39
00:05:46,710 --> 00:05:48,450
But now that I know who it is,

40
00:05:49,080 --> 00:05:50,478
I have a bad feeling.

41
00:05:50,479 --> 00:05:51,590
What feeling?

42
00:05:52,320 --> 00:05:54,090
I think it will last a while.

43
00:05:59,390 --> 00:06:00,890
Let's wait and see.

44
00:06:01,530 --> 00:06:03,329
If we disapprove when they're fired up,

45
00:06:03,330 --> 00:06:05,299
it might even bring them closer.

46
00:06:08,439 --> 00:06:10,669
Did you go and do something already?

47
00:06:11,239 --> 00:06:14,510
Well, I got a bit physical and violent.

48
00:06:14,780 --> 00:06:15,809
With her?

49
00:06:15,939 --> 00:06:17,640
Are you crazy?

50
00:06:21,080 --> 00:06:24,520
I'm so sorry. I must've been exhausted.

51
00:06:25,189 --> 00:06:26,189
I just got up.

52
00:06:27,249 --> 00:06:28,460
I didn't wake you on purpose.

53
00:06:29,189 --> 00:06:30,989
I'll take the subway. Don't worry.

54
00:06:32,760 --> 00:06:33,859
See you later.

55
00:06:58,749 --> 00:07:00,689
(Daechi Chase)

56
00:07:03,789 --> 00:07:04,859
Hello.

57
00:07:05,260 --> 00:07:06,260
Hello.

58
00:07:09,059 --> 00:07:10,200
Hello.

59
00:07:10,799 --> 00:07:12,030
(Daechi Chase)

60
00:07:14,570 --> 00:07:15,570
Good morning.

61
00:07:17,039 --> 00:07:18,369
As if it is.

62
00:07:19,640 --> 00:07:21,840
- Hello. - Hello.

63
00:07:23,979 --> 00:07:25,010
Hello.

64
00:07:42,700 --> 00:07:44,059
Min Hui Ju's not coming?

65
00:07:45,129 --> 00:07:46,200
She's on her way.

66
00:07:51,169 --> 00:07:54,410
Shall we get started first?

67
00:07:55,479 --> 00:07:56,910
I hate this.

68
00:08:07,350 --> 00:08:08,390
So,

69
00:08:09,220 --> 00:08:11,160
it's as I said in the message yesterday.

70
00:08:11,760 --> 00:08:13,189
What I object to is the fact...

71
00:08:13,590 --> 00:08:15,260
that someone was prioritized...

72
00:08:15,999 --> 00:08:18,299
in the use of our academy's main resources.

73
00:08:31,239 --> 00:08:32,280
I want in.

74
00:08:37,050 --> 00:08:39,550
Hey, Mom. Did Byeol get a shot?

75
00:08:40,889 --> 00:08:42,759
It's a long wait to see the pediatrician, isn't it?

76
00:08:43,790 --> 00:08:47,330
No, I don't have a new schedule. I just have a meeting.

77
00:08:48,759 --> 00:08:51,060
No, take her to your place, not mine.

78
00:08:51,729 --> 00:08:52,970
Our place is a mess.

79
00:08:53,830 --> 00:08:54,899
Yes.

80
00:08:59,970 --> 00:09:01,479
Come here.

81
00:09:20,889 --> 00:09:22,700
Go somewhere and kill some time.

82
00:09:23,200 --> 00:09:25,800
I'll tell you what the others said.

83
00:09:26,869 --> 00:09:27,970
I'll clarify.

84
00:09:30,769 --> 00:09:31,769
"Clarify?"

85
00:09:32,840 --> 00:09:33,869
You'll explain?

86
00:09:36,080 --> 00:09:39,279
That won't solve the issue is why.

87
00:09:40,409 --> 00:09:41,978
They're all well-educated,

88
00:09:41,979 --> 00:09:43,420
and they all teach.

89
00:09:44,550 --> 00:09:46,648
If I explain rationally...

90
00:09:46,649 --> 00:09:48,090
Come on.

91
00:09:48,659 --> 00:09:51,690
Jun Ho. Mr. Lee.

92
00:09:53,330 --> 00:09:56,099
They're well-educated, and they teach.

93
00:09:56,100 --> 00:09:58,029
And that's why it's a problem.

94
00:10:00,729 --> 00:10:01,840
What do you mean?

95
00:10:03,200 --> 00:10:05,639
They're all rational,

96
00:10:05,769 --> 00:10:07,269
and that's why things will snowball.

97
00:10:08,310 --> 00:10:10,878
You have no idea how many people...

98
00:10:10,879 --> 00:10:13,009
inside and out want Hye Jin to go down.

99
00:10:21,489 --> 00:10:24,220
Mr. Lee. You're stubborn.

100
00:10:29,430 --> 00:10:30,800
Shall I tell you a scary story?

101
00:10:33,529 --> 00:10:34,899
It's about another neighborhood.

102
00:10:35,340 --> 00:10:38,238
An instructor who taught the most students from a school...

103
00:10:38,239 --> 00:10:39,310
got cancer.

104
00:10:40,170 --> 00:10:42,179
It was in the early stages and easy to handle.

105
00:10:42,180 --> 00:10:43,180
But...

106
00:10:43,840 --> 00:10:45,180
in less than 24 hours,

107
00:10:45,649 --> 00:10:48,849
a rumor spread that the teacher was terminal...

108
00:10:48,850 --> 00:10:50,149
and didn't have long to live.

109
00:10:51,590 --> 00:10:55,460
That's the rumor others started so they could steal the students.

110
00:10:57,920 --> 00:10:59,359
That's the world we live in.

111
00:11:04,200 --> 00:11:06,800
You and Hye Jin.

112
00:11:08,139 --> 00:11:09,170
I don't think...

113
00:11:09,970 --> 00:11:12,909
you would have done something terrible.

114
00:11:16,310 --> 00:11:17,379
So...

115
00:11:18,450 --> 00:11:20,479
go somewhere and have a coffee...

116
00:11:21,350 --> 00:11:22,379
and wait.

117
00:11:23,279 --> 00:11:24,279
Okay?

118
00:11:26,649 --> 00:11:28,460
I asked who called Ms. Seo.

119
00:11:29,220 --> 00:11:31,059
Please hear me out. I'll keep it short.

120
00:11:31,060 --> 00:11:32,190
Who told her about this?

121
00:11:32,729 --> 00:11:33,759
I did.

122
00:11:34,290 --> 00:11:35,359
What?

123
00:11:36,659 --> 00:11:37,759
Will you excuse us?

124
00:11:38,499 --> 00:11:39,600
Can't we...

125
00:11:40,129 --> 00:11:43,170
hear what she has to say?

126
00:11:44,800 --> 00:11:48,839
That will make it harder to make an objective decision.

127
00:11:48,840 --> 00:11:51,608
I don't know if this is an issue that needs explaining.

128
00:11:51,609 --> 00:11:52,778
Wait.

129
00:11:52,779 --> 00:11:55,550
This isn't just about a couple dating.

130
00:11:56,749 --> 00:11:58,690
A team leader at an academy,

131
00:11:59,950 --> 00:12:01,859
a main instructor of all people...

132
00:12:02,560 --> 00:12:03,858
used her authority...

133
00:12:03,859 --> 00:12:05,889
and showered a new recruit with privileges...

134
00:12:06,060 --> 00:12:08,200
and benefits and that's what I object to.

135
00:12:08,800 --> 00:12:10,359
The ad was weird.

136
00:12:11,670 --> 00:12:13,930
"A teacher and student sally forth." So old-fashioned.

137
00:12:14,269 --> 00:12:15,769
I'll start with that ad.

138
00:12:16,769 --> 00:12:19,739
- Heewon High was always... - Shouldn't you...

139
00:12:20,310 --> 00:12:23,239
start by saying whether or not you are dating?

140
00:12:23,479 --> 00:12:24,479
Gosh.

141
00:12:27,450 --> 00:12:28,879
Mr. Lee is...

142
00:12:32,190 --> 00:12:33,249
He is...

143
00:12:43,700 --> 00:12:44,999
What's this?

144
00:12:45,529 --> 00:12:47,700
Are you moving as a team now?

145
00:12:52,170 --> 00:12:53,210
Or did you...

146
00:12:54,269 --> 00:12:56,639
decide to host a tearful press conference?

147
00:12:57,580 --> 00:12:58,609
It's not that.

148
00:12:59,180 --> 00:13:00,608
I didn't know Ms. Seo was here, and...

149
00:13:00,609 --> 00:13:02,248
As if you don't know.

150
00:13:02,249 --> 00:13:03,850
You practically live together.

151
00:13:20,700 --> 00:13:21,769
Mr. Lee Myeong Jun.

152
00:13:23,869 --> 00:13:25,469
Yes? What?

153
00:13:25,470 --> 00:13:27,369
Can I speak as equals, man to man?

154
00:13:29,279 --> 00:13:30,279
What?

155
00:13:38,119 --> 00:13:39,519
(Problems With Colonial Modernization Theory)

156
00:13:41,249 --> 00:13:43,190
Son. Mom's going out.

157
00:13:43,989 --> 00:13:45,290
- Already? - Yes, I'm busy.

158
00:13:53,399 --> 00:13:55,499
Is it about the text you got yesterday?

159
00:13:57,869 --> 00:13:59,638
What's the big deal...

160
00:13:59,639 --> 00:14:01,639
about two instructors seeing each other?

161
00:14:02,580 --> 00:14:05,310
Weren't you the one who vouched for Jun Ho's class?

162
00:14:06,009 --> 00:14:07,509
You don't know what you're talking about.

163
00:14:08,050 --> 00:14:09,149
What don't I know?

164
00:14:09,649 --> 00:14:10,680
How a parent feels.

165
00:14:11,519 --> 00:14:12,519
What does that mean?

166
00:14:13,920 --> 00:14:17,319
These days, to send one kid to a decent university,

167
00:14:17,320 --> 00:14:20,060
both parents and even the grandparents...

168
00:14:20,229 --> 00:14:23,159
put in money, effort, and trust into instructors.

169
00:14:23,359 --> 00:14:25,470
And to think they get up to no good at work?

170
00:14:25,729 --> 00:14:27,430
I can't let someone like that teach my kid.

171
00:14:27,629 --> 00:14:28,840
What do you mean by "no good?"

172
00:14:29,399 --> 00:14:32,138
What kind of talk has been going around during the night?

173
00:14:32,139 --> 00:14:33,909
That's how things will turn out soon.

174
00:14:35,080 --> 00:14:36,180
Goodness.

175
00:14:38,609 --> 00:14:39,649
It has begun.

176
00:14:42,450 --> 00:14:44,249
Hello, you're A Jeong's mom, right?

177
00:14:45,320 --> 00:14:46,519
Yes.

178
00:14:46,649 --> 00:14:48,320
It's pretty early for a call.

179
00:14:48,859 --> 00:14:51,220
What? No, it's fine.

180
00:15:09,909 --> 00:15:12,810
Hey. I think the rumor about you got weird.

181
00:15:23,720 --> 00:15:24,720
Are you okay?

182
00:15:34,070 --> 00:15:35,839
You two got up to no good,

183
00:15:35,840 --> 00:15:37,469
and you're saying what now?

184
00:15:37,470 --> 00:15:39,738
I said I felt sorry for the kids you teach!

185
00:15:39,739 --> 00:15:41,709
- What? How dare you? - Stop it!

186
00:15:41,710 --> 00:15:44,009
- You, come here. - You think I can't?

187
00:15:44,139 --> 00:15:47,210
Who gave you the right to call me names?

188
00:15:47,310 --> 00:15:49,279
Did you hear what he said?

189
00:15:49,450 --> 00:15:51,790
The kids will start coming in soon. Will you stop it?

190
00:15:52,019 --> 00:15:53,519
Let go! I'm calming down.

191
00:15:54,320 --> 00:15:55,960
My gosh. Who does he think he is?

192
00:15:56,119 --> 00:15:57,189
- Mr. Yoon. - Darn it.

193
00:15:57,190 --> 00:15:58,758
- That's enough. - Did you see that?

194
00:15:58,759 --> 00:16:00,858
- This isn't right, is it? - Are you defending him?

195
00:16:00,859 --> 00:16:02,358
- He came after me. - What?

196
00:16:02,359 --> 00:16:03,429
- Please. - Let me go.

197
00:16:03,430 --> 00:16:06,299
- Come here! - We need to talk calmly.

198
00:16:06,300 --> 00:16:07,700
What good is that?

199
00:16:08,229 --> 00:16:09,768
Jun Ho's reaction explained it all.

200
00:16:09,769 --> 00:16:11,369
- Mr. Yoon. - This blows.

201
00:16:11,869 --> 00:16:13,508
I don't believe this.

202
00:16:13,509 --> 00:16:14,509
Ms. Seo.

203
00:16:15,379 --> 00:16:17,509
I don't think you have time for this.

204
00:16:22,249 --> 00:16:23,320
Okay, thanks.

205
00:16:28,790 --> 00:16:29,790
Why give me this?

206
00:16:30,019 --> 00:16:31,290
You have nicer handwriting.

207
00:16:31,489 --> 00:16:33,290
I haven't written anything in years.

208
00:16:33,790 --> 00:16:34,790
What should I write?

209
00:16:35,529 --> 00:16:38,499
"Thank you so much for the good results in the finals."

210
00:16:38,700 --> 00:16:40,200
"Help us out in the coming year too."

211
00:16:40,769 --> 00:16:43,170
Isn't that something I should say to the teachers?

212
00:16:43,700 --> 00:16:45,969
We pay your instructors every month.

213
00:16:45,970 --> 00:16:47,570
Do you know how much that is?

214
00:16:48,680 --> 00:16:49,878
Go to your academy after this.

215
00:16:49,879 --> 00:16:50,979
After a short prayer.

216
00:16:58,080 --> 00:16:59,590
- Sung Ha Yul. - What?

217
00:17:00,249 --> 00:17:02,690
Give me Seo Hye Jin's printouts and homework.

218
00:17:03,519 --> 00:17:05,019
Here? Right now?

219
00:17:05,119 --> 00:17:06,129
Do as I say.

220
00:17:19,939 --> 00:17:20,968
(Full-mark Korean)

221
00:17:20,969 --> 00:17:22,010
Here.

222
00:17:23,280 --> 00:17:24,310
Where's the rest?

223
00:17:24,939 --> 00:17:26,310
There were no printouts,

224
00:17:26,679 --> 00:17:28,850
and the homework was to read the next chapter.

225
00:17:29,619 --> 00:17:31,250
- Is that all? - Yes.

226
00:17:31,449 --> 00:17:33,350
She suggested we change how we study.

227
00:17:36,119 --> 00:17:37,119
She must be crazy.

228
00:17:54,909 --> 00:17:56,480
Hello, Shin Dae Baek speaking.

229
00:18:00,280 --> 00:18:02,280
Yes. Why are you calling me?

230
00:18:05,790 --> 00:18:08,490
Yes, I do work at Daechi Chase.

231
00:18:11,619 --> 00:18:12,629
Yes.

232
00:18:21,969 --> 00:18:25,810
I don't see how this is something you'd call me about.

233
00:18:29,580 --> 00:18:31,439
You said you'd explain rationally.

234
00:18:31,909 --> 00:18:33,480
What have you done?

235
00:18:36,350 --> 00:18:37,350
Drink this.

236
00:18:41,419 --> 00:18:42,459
Thank you.

237
00:18:44,760 --> 00:18:47,389
Drink that and get a strong hold of yourself.

238
00:18:52,230 --> 00:18:54,469
What happened here might be nothing at all.

239
00:18:55,199 --> 00:18:56,199
Outside...

240
00:18:58,100 --> 00:18:59,540
I think it's much worse.

241
00:19:00,469 --> 00:19:03,878
Jung Soo takes pretty good notes compared to most kids,

242
00:19:03,879 --> 00:19:05,579
and he concentrates in class.

243
00:19:05,580 --> 00:19:06,649
Yes.

244
00:19:06,750 --> 00:19:08,919
But his books show no signs that he studied.

245
00:19:09,050 --> 00:19:10,619
That goes for Ye Eun too.

246
00:19:11,280 --> 00:19:12,590
Don't you think something's off?

247
00:19:13,050 --> 00:19:14,618
She used to give out loads of homework,

248
00:19:14,619 --> 00:19:16,289
packs of printouts,

249
00:19:16,290 --> 00:19:18,260
and mock exams for the kids to go through.

250
00:19:18,629 --> 00:19:20,458
She said she'd stop checking their homework.

251
00:19:20,459 --> 00:19:23,599
Doesn't that mean she gave up monitoring the kids altogether?

252
00:19:23,600 --> 00:19:26,168
She doesn't even grade the homework herself.

253
00:19:26,169 --> 00:19:27,369
Her TA does.

254
00:19:27,399 --> 00:19:29,299
- Gosh. - Goodness.

255
00:19:29,300 --> 00:19:31,639
Oh, forget it.

256
00:19:33,169 --> 00:19:34,939
Is she short on energy?

257
00:19:36,280 --> 00:19:37,280
Because he's younger?

258
00:19:38,879 --> 00:19:40,409
Watch what you say.

259
00:19:40,909 --> 00:19:41,949
Excuse me.

260
00:19:42,419 --> 00:19:44,020
You mean Seo Hye Jin, right?

261
00:19:44,850 --> 00:19:45,850
Yes.

262
00:19:47,649 --> 00:19:49,219
Could we join you?

263
00:19:49,790 --> 00:19:51,359
Yes, I guess?

264
00:19:54,659 --> 00:19:55,699
(Full-mark Korean)

265
00:20:04,199 --> 00:20:06,139
- Is your kid in tenth grade? - Yes.

266
00:20:07,169 --> 00:20:08,169
So is mine.

267
00:20:10,879 --> 00:20:13,409
This is no laughing matter.

268
00:20:15,780 --> 00:20:17,719
That instructor whom she taught.

269
00:20:18,050 --> 00:20:19,719
- Lee Jun Ho? - Yes.

270
00:20:20,790 --> 00:20:22,520
He used to work at Jungwon Group.

271
00:20:23,219 --> 00:20:24,520
What about it?

272
00:20:25,689 --> 00:20:27,759
To make a man leave a perfectly fine job...

273
00:20:27,760 --> 00:20:29,429
to teach at an academy.

274
00:20:29,929 --> 00:20:31,859
Do you think that was an easy feat?

275
00:20:33,199 --> 00:20:34,270
What?

276
00:20:35,469 --> 00:20:37,499
When Seo Hye Jin first came here,

277
00:20:37,500 --> 00:20:39,669
Lee Jun Ho was her only student.

278
00:20:41,439 --> 00:20:44,510
Perhaps back in the day, Seo Hye Jin gave him...

279
00:20:47,449 --> 00:20:49,820
an experience he could never forget.

280
00:20:51,919 --> 00:20:53,489
- No. - No.

281
00:20:53,490 --> 00:20:55,490
- You went too far. - Yes.

282
00:20:56,889 --> 00:20:58,520
Do you have a daughter?

283
00:20:59,359 --> 00:21:00,359
Yes.

284
00:21:00,629 --> 00:21:02,129
I have a son, so I know.

285
00:21:02,659 --> 00:21:04,260
Teenage boys.

286
00:21:05,469 --> 00:21:07,800
They're so virile and full of energy.

287
00:21:09,240 --> 00:21:12,369
- Oh, gosh. No way. - If that's really true...

288
00:21:12,609 --> 00:21:14,668
- That's disgusting. - Hi.

289
00:21:14,669 --> 00:21:16,479
What's disgusting?

290
00:21:16,480 --> 00:21:18,540
Something crazy is going on. Sit down.

291
00:21:18,879 --> 00:21:20,709
- Gosh... - Oh, no...

292
00:21:21,149 --> 00:21:23,019
(Choisun will become the best.)

293
00:21:23,020 --> 00:21:25,219
That's how crazy they were.

294
00:21:26,050 --> 00:21:28,618
They stayed behind alone in classrooms.

295
00:21:28,619 --> 00:21:31,020
- Oh, gosh. - In a classroom?

296
00:21:32,590 --> 00:21:33,958
- Hello. - Hello.

297
00:21:33,959 --> 00:21:34,990
Director.

298
00:21:35,959 --> 00:21:36,959
It's incredible.

299
00:21:38,330 --> 00:21:40,629
As soon as you hired Pyo Sang Seob,

300
00:21:40,730 --> 00:21:42,869
Daechi Chase seemed to implode.

301
00:21:43,699 --> 00:21:46,169
This must be your lucky year.

302
00:21:46,770 --> 00:21:48,439
What are you talking about?

303
00:21:48,540 --> 00:21:49,908
You know Seo Hye Jin, right?

304
00:21:49,909 --> 00:21:52,009
The one who taught with her ex-student.

305
00:21:52,010 --> 00:21:54,080
I know who that is. What about her?

306
00:21:56,679 --> 00:21:58,379
That ex-student instructor...

307
00:21:59,719 --> 00:22:00,820
was her lover.

308
00:22:01,550 --> 00:22:02,619
Since he was in school.

309
00:22:03,889 --> 00:22:04,889
Really?

310
00:22:05,459 --> 00:22:07,590
I don't think this will go away quietly.

311
00:22:09,000 --> 00:22:11,899
Oh, dear. What a shame.

312
00:22:12,500 --> 00:22:13,969
She's a good teacher.

313
00:22:15,469 --> 00:22:17,500
(Choisun Academy)

314
00:22:32,790 --> 00:22:34,020
Seo Hye Jin.

315
00:22:36,159 --> 00:22:37,389
What a waste.

316
00:22:41,889 --> 00:22:42,929
Come in.

317
00:22:46,600 --> 00:22:49,500
You came right on time.

318
00:22:49,600 --> 00:22:51,040
Director Choi.

319
00:22:51,169 --> 00:22:54,270
You prosper each day, and I'm pleased for you.

320
00:22:54,740 --> 00:22:55,740
Thank you.

321
00:22:56,040 --> 00:22:57,379
- Take a seat. - Okay.

322
00:23:00,679 --> 00:23:02,949
I'd recommend this property...

323
00:23:03,949 --> 00:23:05,550
and this one.

324
00:23:05,820 --> 00:23:08,618
They both used to be academies,

325
00:23:08,619 --> 00:23:11,619
so you'll save money on setting things up.

326
00:23:12,090 --> 00:23:13,629
And it's close to this place too.

327
00:23:15,159 --> 00:23:17,099
The owner of this property...

328
00:23:17,100 --> 00:23:19,399
just turned 30 years old.

329
00:23:19,500 --> 00:23:22,129
He spends half the year traveling the world.

330
00:23:22,500 --> 00:23:24,438
He put my office in charge of management.

331
00:23:24,439 --> 00:23:25,969
That would benefit you too.

332
00:23:27,869 --> 00:23:30,179
Shall I arrange a formal meeting?

333
00:23:30,280 --> 00:23:31,340
No.

334
00:23:33,449 --> 00:23:35,980
There's a building I have in mind.

335
00:23:36,050 --> 00:23:39,189
Oh, okay. Tell me which one it is.

336
00:23:39,550 --> 00:23:43,020
Do you know Daechi Chase that's on the main road?

337
00:23:43,290 --> 00:23:44,359
I do.

338
00:23:45,189 --> 00:23:47,659
I don't think there are any empty floors in that building.

339
00:23:48,629 --> 00:23:50,600
I have a feeling there will be a few soon.

340
00:23:52,869 --> 00:23:55,639
I want to move into the floor...

341
00:23:55,899 --> 00:23:57,399
they have the classrooms on.

342
00:23:58,669 --> 00:23:59,810
I'll look into it.

343
00:24:01,939 --> 00:24:03,040
Thank you.

344
00:24:20,590 --> 00:24:21,760
What's going on?

345
00:24:24,330 --> 00:24:25,929
Check your online messenger.

346
00:24:27,100 --> 00:24:29,839
Won't everyone associated with Ms. Seo go down?

347
00:24:29,840 --> 00:24:32,270
Do you think she'll go down just like that?

348
00:24:46,619 --> 00:24:47,619
Let's go outside.

349
00:24:48,990 --> 00:24:49,990
I'm fine.

350
00:24:51,820 --> 00:24:54,389
Don't sit here and let everyone stare.

351
00:24:54,530 --> 00:24:55,730
We did nothing wrong.

352
00:24:56,530 --> 00:24:57,730
There's no reason to run away.

353
00:25:05,300 --> 00:25:06,369
Hey.

354
00:25:07,969 --> 00:25:10,480
Why are the director and vice-director so quiet?

355
00:25:12,780 --> 00:25:13,780
I don't know.

356
00:25:21,889 --> 00:25:24,790
Why did you come this far this early in the day?

357
00:25:33,000 --> 00:25:34,469
Is there something we can't discuss at work?

358
00:25:37,840 --> 00:25:40,409
I rushed over wondering if I should go on my knees.

359
00:25:41,540 --> 00:25:43,480
Gosh. That's a bit much.

360
00:25:50,480 --> 00:25:51,480
Goodness.

361
00:25:54,389 --> 00:25:57,859
I got about 500 calls this morning.

362
00:25:58,619 --> 00:26:01,358
I think I'll get about 5,000 more.

363
00:26:01,359 --> 00:26:03,198
Then you should go and sort it out...

364
00:26:03,199 --> 00:26:04,760
instead of coming here.

365
00:26:06,300 --> 00:26:09,240
Beating around the bush will only be a waste of time.

366
00:26:09,840 --> 00:26:11,240
I'll ask you point blank.

367
00:26:13,040 --> 00:26:15,209
Why on earth as you doing this?

368
00:26:16,679 --> 00:26:17,709
Why?

369
00:26:18,609 --> 00:26:20,709
I'm just trying to take my share.

370
00:26:21,010 --> 00:26:24,550
We got along well so far.

371
00:26:24,820 --> 00:26:26,750
Who got along well? Us?

372
00:26:29,320 --> 00:26:32,429
Well, there were times when we butted heads...

373
00:26:32,959 --> 00:26:34,989
on how to run the academy...

374
00:26:34,990 --> 00:26:36,459
and how to manage our staff,

375
00:26:36,959 --> 00:26:38,658
but we were pretty democratic...

376
00:26:38,659 --> 00:26:40,629
I have too long to live.

377
00:26:41,330 --> 00:26:43,539
Way too long to spend it working for...

378
00:26:43,540 --> 00:26:45,500
democratic Kim Hyun Tak for a fixed salary.

379
00:26:46,469 --> 00:26:49,208
If I'm unlucky, I might have to live longer...

380
00:26:49,209 --> 00:26:51,080
than I already have.

381
00:26:52,879 --> 00:26:56,350
Today is the youngest I'll ever be,

382
00:26:56,649 --> 00:26:59,189
and I want to get fired up and bloom.

383
00:27:00,590 --> 00:27:01,619
That fire.

384
00:27:02,619 --> 00:27:04,659
Couldn't we set it together?

385
00:27:09,429 --> 00:27:11,530
If you tell me what you want...

386
00:27:16,169 --> 00:27:17,199
If I tell you,

387
00:27:18,139 --> 00:27:19,409
will you give it to me?

388
00:27:22,209 --> 00:27:24,179
Even if I can't give you all you ask,

389
00:27:24,740 --> 00:27:27,709
couldn't we at least discuss and agree...

390
00:27:28,050 --> 00:27:30,079
on something that works for us both?

391
00:27:30,080 --> 00:27:32,249
It's pointless if you can't give me all I ask.

392
00:27:32,250 --> 00:27:35,859
Actually, even if you give me all I ask, it's not enough.

393
00:27:36,090 --> 00:27:39,260
What I want is the academy you took from me.

394
00:27:39,929 --> 00:27:41,230
My goodness.

395
00:27:42,330 --> 00:27:45,330
Don't talk like I stole Victoria Academy.

396
00:27:45,800 --> 00:27:47,769
What we did benefited us both at the time.

397
00:27:47,770 --> 00:27:50,439
I was the easiest prey within your grasp.

398
00:27:51,300 --> 00:27:53,269
It was when I was short on cash...

399
00:27:53,270 --> 00:27:55,040
because I was expanding it.

400
00:27:55,340 --> 00:27:57,510
Okay. At the time,

401
00:27:58,439 --> 00:28:00,349
I'd won over your teachers already,

402
00:28:00,350 --> 00:28:02,280
so I bought you out pretty cheap.

403
00:28:02,520 --> 00:28:05,280
But I made you vice-director, and that compensation...

404
00:28:05,379 --> 00:28:06,419
was more than enough...

405
00:28:10,020 --> 00:28:12,790
You think that was more than enough.

406
00:28:13,359 --> 00:28:15,290
That's why we can't reach an agreement.

407
00:28:17,060 --> 00:28:18,060
Help me out here.

408
00:28:19,429 --> 00:28:21,969
Hye Jin's about to lose all her students.

409
00:28:22,169 --> 00:28:23,769
If the instructors leave too,

410
00:28:23,770 --> 00:28:26,509
I'll have to close down next month.

411
00:28:26,510 --> 00:28:27,908
It wouldn't be...

412
00:28:27,909 --> 00:28:30,310
a bad idea to start over, then.

413
00:28:34,310 --> 00:28:37,050
Today is the youngest you'll ever be.

414
00:28:41,090 --> 00:28:42,689
You can't do this.

415
00:28:46,459 --> 00:28:48,830
I get that you have a lot against me.

416
00:28:49,699 --> 00:28:51,959
But what did Hye Jin do?

417
00:28:52,899 --> 00:28:55,938
She's good enough that she can start over...

418
00:28:55,939 --> 00:28:57,699
- anywhere else. - Ms. Woo.

419
00:28:57,969 --> 00:28:58,969
That's it.

420
00:29:01,040 --> 00:29:03,709
I'll send my resignation by email.

421
00:29:03,879 --> 00:29:06,050
No, wait. Ms. Woo.

422
00:29:08,480 --> 00:29:09,480
What...

423
00:29:27,199 --> 00:29:28,199
Help me.

424
00:29:32,040 --> 00:29:33,540
Let me explain.

425
00:29:33,969 --> 00:29:36,340
The instructors need to stay...

426
00:29:40,379 --> 00:29:41,679
Sorry.

427
00:29:42,879 --> 00:29:44,020
I can't believe...

428
00:29:44,649 --> 00:29:46,790
how little influence you have now.

429
00:29:49,959 --> 00:29:52,218
At least let us last another semester...

430
00:29:52,219 --> 00:29:55,330
Why are you going overboard?

431
00:29:55,859 --> 00:29:57,399
It's not like you own this academy.

432
00:29:57,760 --> 00:29:59,300
I wouldn't be asking if it were mine.

433
00:30:00,669 --> 00:30:02,300
What did Director Kim do to deserve this?

434
00:30:06,240 --> 00:30:07,369
Ms. Woo said...

435
00:30:08,840 --> 00:30:09,939
I should've listened...

436
00:30:10,409 --> 00:30:12,609
when she suggested we squash some of the power you have.

437
00:30:15,850 --> 00:30:17,080
She was right.

438
00:30:20,119 --> 00:30:21,719
That's who Woo Seung Hui is.

439
00:30:26,060 --> 00:30:29,260
The thoughts one keeps buried deep inside?

440
00:30:29,859 --> 00:30:32,899
She has a knack for sniffing out the musty scent they give off.

441
00:30:33,869 --> 00:30:35,800
Director Kim's anxiety.

442
00:30:35,969 --> 00:30:38,239
Lee Myeong Jun's insecurity. The White Haired Witch's greed.

443
00:30:38,240 --> 00:30:40,168
She took advantage of that, and now with you...

444
00:30:40,169 --> 00:30:41,169
No way.

445
00:30:43,280 --> 00:30:45,980
So this is how people change when they're cornered.

446
00:30:46,510 --> 00:30:49,149
- You're badmouthing others. - This isn't me talking smack.

447
00:30:55,290 --> 00:30:56,719
Know your place.

448
00:30:58,689 --> 00:31:01,060
You're the reason the academy imploded, not me.

449
00:31:02,359 --> 00:31:03,800
All because you're head over heels for your young student.

450
00:31:09,300 --> 00:31:10,439
Take the call.

451
00:31:11,240 --> 00:31:14,169
Your time will be better spent explaining yourself to the mothers.

452
00:31:22,879 --> 00:31:23,919
Yes, ma'am.

453
00:31:29,490 --> 00:31:31,189
I understand, ma'am,

454
00:31:31,260 --> 00:31:33,958
but have you discussed this with Do Gyeom?

455
00:31:33,959 --> 00:31:35,760
I'm afraid there's a long wait list...

456
00:31:37,300 --> 00:31:39,060
for Chanyoung High consultations.

457
00:31:42,000 --> 00:31:44,300
Leave your contact information, and we'll call.

458
00:31:45,240 --> 00:31:46,240
Sure.

459
00:31:46,340 --> 00:31:49,480
Ma'am, it's not what you think.

460
00:31:49,639 --> 00:31:50,879
Of course not...

461
00:31:51,109 --> 00:31:53,349
A minor, you say?

462
00:31:53,350 --> 00:31:55,409
Ma'am, can you hold?

463
00:31:55,449 --> 00:31:56,979
This is Daechi Chase... Yes.

464
00:31:56,980 --> 00:31:58,878
I see. Just a second.

465
00:31:58,879 --> 00:32:01,750
Ma'am, let me call you back. I'm terribly sorry.

466
00:32:01,949 --> 00:32:03,119
Yes?

467
00:32:03,219 --> 00:32:04,459
I see.

468
00:32:04,719 --> 00:32:06,129
May I have a name?

469
00:32:06,830 --> 00:32:09,459
I'm afraid you can't come in for a consultation today.

470
00:32:11,560 --> 00:32:13,529
Of course it isn't that.

471
00:32:13,530 --> 00:32:15,499
- We'll give you a call. - I'm afraid we're fully booked.

472
00:32:15,500 --> 00:32:17,939
Not just the consultations, but also Ms. Seo...

473
00:32:35,119 --> 00:32:37,020
You will be doused in nasty water.

474
00:32:46,530 --> 00:32:48,500
Why are you out here in the cold?

475
00:32:49,300 --> 00:32:50,340
Right.

476
00:32:51,070 --> 00:32:52,169
I just ended up here.

477
00:32:54,639 --> 00:32:57,939
If you're going to be in agony, be so somewhere warm.

478
00:32:58,580 --> 00:33:00,850
- I looked for you everywhere. - I'm not in agony.

479
00:33:01,449 --> 00:33:02,949
The question I raised was aboveboard.

480
00:33:06,649 --> 00:33:08,189
That's how far you'll go.

481
00:33:12,760 --> 00:33:13,760
What do you mean?

482
00:33:15,490 --> 00:33:17,560
Ms. Seo's in a huge mess with just the rumors...

483
00:33:17,959 --> 00:33:19,668
that have been spreading outside.

484
00:33:19,669 --> 00:33:21,199
I didn't cause any of that.

485
00:33:21,330 --> 00:33:22,840
No matter who did it...

486
00:33:27,609 --> 00:33:28,609
Wait.

487
00:33:30,340 --> 00:33:32,408
That sounds like there was someone else...

488
00:33:32,409 --> 00:33:33,980
in charge of spreading those rumors.

489
00:33:35,409 --> 00:33:37,619
It also sounds like the whole attack was coordinated by a mastermind.

490
00:33:38,719 --> 00:33:39,750
Am I right?

491
00:33:39,990 --> 00:33:41,490
I have a class I must go to.

492
00:33:42,990 --> 00:33:44,789
Could that person be...

493
00:33:44,790 --> 00:33:46,020
I have a class.

494
00:33:50,699 --> 00:33:53,000
Was it Ms. Woo?

495
00:33:54,770 --> 00:33:57,500
And did Lee Myeong Jun spread the rumors?

496
00:34:00,740 --> 00:34:01,810
Darn.

497
00:34:10,080 --> 00:34:13,049
Ms. Woo will soon make an offer.

498
00:34:14,089 --> 00:34:16,389
Seriously consider it. The ship we're on is sinking.

499
00:34:18,089 --> 00:34:21,429
You people are like trash.

500
00:34:23,330 --> 00:34:25,759
What did you just call me?

501
00:34:31,900 --> 00:34:33,170
Let's set the record straight.

502
00:34:34,909 --> 00:34:37,409
She'll be fine if we support her together...

503
00:34:37,679 --> 00:34:39,210
and clear the air regarding the rumor.

504
00:34:39,509 --> 00:34:41,409
- We can take it all back. - For what though?

505
00:34:43,250 --> 00:34:45,779
Think about how much Ms. Seo is hurting.

506
00:34:49,489 --> 00:34:50,489
Mr. Yoon.

507
00:34:52,759 --> 00:34:53,830
You'll most certainly...

508
00:34:55,460 --> 00:34:57,060
regret this.

509
00:34:59,029 --> 00:35:00,069
Sure.

510
00:35:01,069 --> 00:35:02,400
And I'm sorry about that.

511
00:35:09,710 --> 00:35:11,079
The textbooks being clean doesn't mean...

512
00:35:11,080 --> 00:35:12,839
they haven't been studying.

513
00:35:13,750 --> 00:35:15,879
I'm helping students who have trouble with reading...

514
00:35:15,880 --> 00:35:17,350
learn the basics.

515
00:35:18,020 --> 00:35:19,849
We feel like...

516
00:35:19,850 --> 00:35:22,249
you've abruptly changed your style of teaching.

517
00:35:22,250 --> 00:35:23,719
We're worried about progress as well.

518
00:35:24,089 --> 00:35:26,059
It doesn't seem like you'll be able...

519
00:35:26,060 --> 00:35:27,589
to teach all that's on the syllabus.

520
00:35:29,860 --> 00:35:32,659
Jung Soo is a top student when it comes to Korean.

521
00:35:33,270 --> 00:35:35,829
He achieved first class on his finals,

522
00:35:35,830 --> 00:35:37,139
and I was over the moon.

523
00:35:37,600 --> 00:35:38,839
Gosh.

524
00:35:38,940 --> 00:35:40,369
He did well on the KSAT mock exam as well.

525
00:35:41,069 --> 00:35:42,110
I see.

526
00:35:42,940 --> 00:35:45,040
But I don't think Jung Soo...

527
00:35:45,739 --> 00:35:47,980
will be able to maintain his grade in 12th grade.

528
00:35:49,179 --> 00:35:50,480
- Sorry? - My gosh.

529
00:35:51,549 --> 00:35:53,149
Are you hoping he won't do well?

530
00:35:53,150 --> 00:35:54,888
No, this is me reflecting on myself.

531
00:35:54,889 --> 00:35:56,589
My way of teaching will fail him.

532
00:35:57,060 --> 00:35:59,290
Kids will fluster after coming across unfamiliar passages...

533
00:35:59,460 --> 00:36:01,889
and will panic with passages they haven't studied.

534
00:36:02,259 --> 00:36:03,829
Ha Yul, Ye Eun,

535
00:36:03,830 --> 00:36:05,730
Jung Soo, Sang Hui, and U Ju.

536
00:36:05,960 --> 00:36:07,468
With every new school year,

537
00:36:07,469 --> 00:36:10,270
they will gradually grow less confident.

538
00:36:11,569 --> 00:36:12,599
With this new method,

539
00:36:12,600 --> 00:36:15,069
can you guarantee a first class grade?

540
00:36:17,179 --> 00:36:19,138
Parents want me to improve the grade...

541
00:36:19,139 --> 00:36:21,309
of a student who lacks basic knowledge and...

542
00:36:21,310 --> 00:36:23,020
You say you'll do it.

543
00:36:23,279 --> 00:36:24,319
Of course...

544
00:36:26,219 --> 00:36:27,219
I can't guarantee it.

545
00:36:27,520 --> 00:36:28,619
- What? - My gosh.

546
00:36:29,049 --> 00:36:32,059
Are you conducting an experiment with our children, then?

547
00:36:32,060 --> 00:36:34,060
I believe I'm on the right track,

548
00:36:34,389 --> 00:36:37,429
but I'm saying I can't promise you results...

549
00:36:37,630 --> 00:36:39,460
